"ClewIntroTutorialTitle" = "Intro to Clew";
"ClewIntroTutorialText" = "Welcome to Clew! Clew helps you navigate and explore indoor spaces by using your phone's camera and inertial sensors. It acts as a 'sighted companion' that helps guide you along a route by providing audio directions and cues. Clew works best within indoor spaces, where GPS doesn't work or is unreliable.";

"introUsingClewTitle" = "Using Clew";
"introUsingClewTextParagraph1" = "Clew helps you find your way around indoors spaces by recording your route when you're going from one place to another. For example, from a lobby area to a room. By recording your route, Clew then helps you navigate your way back to where you started. Clew can help you learn a new environment, so you can confidently navigate it in the future.";

"introUsingClewTextParagraph2" = "Clew is best used indoors. The app doesn't rely on your phone's GPS. This means that Clew is limited in outdoors spaces and for routes over long distances.";

"introClewsRoleTutorialTitle" = "Important Safety Info - Clew's Intended Role";

"introClewsRoleTutorialTextParagraph1" = "Clew is not a substitute for your orientation and mobility skills. It is not a replacement for your white cane, guide dog or primary mobility aid. Clew is intended to work as an additional aid or to complement and enhance your orientation and navigation skills.";

"introClewsRoleTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Please be aware of your surroundings while using the app. It is your responsibility to maintain your personal safety at all times while using Clew.";

"introClewsRoleTutorialTextParagraph3" = "If you are new to Clew, we recommend that you first use the app in an indoor setting that is safe and familiar to you.";

"introClewsRoleTutorialTextParagraph4" = "You acknowledge and agree that your use of the app is at your own risk.";

"introUsingClewTutorialTitle" = "Using This Tutorial";
"introUsingClewTutorialText" = "This tutorial will help you learn the skills needed to use Clew. Each module focuses on a particular skill set and feature of the app. Some of the modules include interactive practice exercises. We recommend that you first use the app in an indoor setting that is safe and familiar to you.";


"orientPhoneTutorialButtonText" = "Holding Your Phone for Best Results";
"orientPhoneTutorialInstructionTextParagraph1" = "Clew uses your phone's camera and inertial sensors to track your position as you move around the environment and when you navigate a route. Holding your phone in the correct pose or orientation is essential in order for the app to work correctly. You should hold your phone in the portrait orientation (vertically), with the rear camera facing forward.";

"orientPhoneTutorialInstructionTextParagraph2" = "It is important to maintain the phone in the vertical pose, with the rear camera facing forward (pointed away from your body) whenever you are navigating or saving a route. Maintaining the phone in this pose helps reduce errors from the app.";


"orientPhoneTutorialInstructionTextParagraph3" = "The following exercise will help you practice holding your phone in the correct pose for Clew. Tap the Practice button to begin.";


"orientPhoneTutorialTipsTitle" = "Tips";
"orientPhoneTutorialTip1" = "Try holding your phone against your chest when you're navigating a route to ensure it remains in the correct vertical pose with the camera facing directly in front of you.";
"orientPhoneTutorialTip2" = "We also recommend that you hold the phone in the opposite hand that you use to work with your white cane or guide dog.";

"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeButton" = "Practicing the Correct Phone Pose";

"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeTitle" = "Practicing the Correct Phone Pose";

"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeInstructionsParagraph1" = "Now you can practice holding your phone in the correct pose for using Clew. Remember that the rear camera should face forward or away from you.";

"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeInstructionsParagraph2" = "Begin the exercise by moving your phone from a horizontal pose to a more vertical pose. Your phone will buzz and make a distinct tone the further you are off from the correct pose. You'll then hear a success chime when you achieve the correct vertical pose. Try moving your phone in and out of the correct pose a couple of times to hear the difference.";

"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeInstructionsParagraph3" = "Now it's your turn. Tap the Start button to begin.";

"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeStart" = "Start";
"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeStop" = "Stop";
"orientPhoneTutorialPracticeSuccess" = "Nice Job! You now know how to hold the phone in the correct pose. You can keep practicing or go to the next section.";


"findPathTutorialButtonText" = "Following a Route";
"findPathTutorialInstructionText" = "Clew will make sounds, haptic feedback and provide directional audio cues whenever you are navigating a route. These distinct sounds, feedback and directional cues enable you to navigate the route correctly. They help you know when you are correctly on the path or if you are slightly off the correct path or have completely deviated from the route.";

"movingOnCorrectPathTitleText" = "Moving Along the Correct Path";
"movingOnCorrectPathInstructionTextParagraph1" = "Whenever you begin navigating a route, you will hear a distinct 'ticking' sound. Clew plays the ticking sound whenever you are correctly aligned to the route. It will play through the entire time until you complete the route, pause or stop navigation.";
"movingOnCorrectPathInstructionTextParagraph2" = "Sighted users will see a colored line showing the correct path on the screen. The path color can be changed in the settings.";

"waypointsTutorialTitleText" = "Waypoints or Virtual Crumbs";
"waypointsTutorialInstructionTextParagraph1" = "Clew provides waypoints or virtual crumbs to keep you in the right orientation as you navigate the route. The app will play a distinct 'chime' when you pass through a waypoint or virtual crumb.";
"waypointsTutorialInstructionTextParagraph2" = "Sighted users will see a colored crumb in the shape of a map point on the screen. The crumb color can be changed in the settings.";

"directionalCuesTutorialTitleText" = "Directional Cues";
"directionalCuesTutorialInstructionText" = "Clew will provide directional cues as soon as you begin navigating a route and to keep oriented correctly. The app will announce directions whenever you pass through a waypoint or virtual crumb. The directional cues include: continue straight, slight right, slight left, turn right, turn left. Clew will also announce when you have reached the end of the route.";

"gettingBackToTheCorrectPathTutorialTitleText" = "Getting Back to the Correct Path";
"gettingBackToTheCorrectPathTutorialInstructionTextParagraph1" = "A distinct tone will play whenever you are off the correct path. This may also happen if your phone is not facing in the direction of the path. If you find yourself off the path, you should stop, try turning around until you hear the 'ticking' sounds that indicate that you're on the correct direction of the path.";
"gettingBackToTheCorrectPathTutorialInstructionTextParagraph2" = "Press the 'Get Directions' button to receive audio directions on how to get back on the route. This is especially helpful if you've become disoriented or off the correct path.";

"findPathPractice1Title" = "Practice Your First Route";
"findPathPractice1InstructionTextParagraph1" = "This first exercise will have you practice the simple route in order to get you accustomed to Clew's sounds and feedback. This first route will guide you forward a few steps and then announce the end of the route. Pay particular attention to the sounds and directional cues.";
"findPathPractice1InstructionTextParagraph2" = "Please make sure that you're in a familiar area with sufficient space to move about before you begin this exercise. ";
"findPathPractice1InstructionTextParagraph3" = "Tap the 'Practice' button and then tap 'Play' to begin the exercise.";

"tutorialRouteAlignmentText" = "To begin the route, tap the \"start navigation\" button below and wait for the countdown.";

"findPathPractice2Title" = "Practice Second Path";
"findPathPractice2InstructionText" = "Here you will practice following a Clew Route. Make sure you are in a familiar place with some open space around you. This path will guide you forward a few steps and then you will pass through a waypoint and be instructed to turn right. Then you will take a few more steps and then arrive. Select begin to enter the practice route.";

"findPathPracticeSuccessTitle" = "Congratulations!";
"findPathPracticeSuccess1Text" = "You've completed your first route. Continue to the next exercise to try another route.";
"findPathPracticeSuccess2Text" = "You now know how to navigate a route! You may continue the tutorial or go to the Home Screen and try performing a Single Use Route. Remember that practice makes perfect!";


"singleUseRouteTutorialButtonText" = "Single Use Routes";

"singleUseRouteTutorialInstructionTextParagraph1" = "Clew's Single Use Routes feature helps you find your way back after going from one place to another. This feature records your path when you walk from point-A to point-B. It then provides you with the return route directions and necessary cues.";

"singleUseRouteTutorialInstructionTextParagraph2" = "For example, you can perform a single use route when going from a lobby area to a room, and then you want to return back to the lobby area.";

"singleUseRouteTutorialInstructionTextParagraph3" = "The Single Use Route allows you to navigate a return route only once. The Save Routes feature allows you to navigate a route multiple times.";

"usingSingleUseRouteTutorialTitle" = "Using Single Use Routes";

"usingSingleUseRouteTutorialTextParagraph1" = "Tap the Single Use Route button on the home screen to activate this feature. Clew will immediately begin recording your route.";

"usingSingleUseRouteTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Now you can navigate to where you want to go. Remember to hold your phone in the correct vertical pose with the rear camera facing forward. Tap the 'stop recording' button once you've arrived at your destination.";

"usingSingleUseRouteTutorialTextParagraph3" = "Tap the 'play' button to initiate the return route navigation. Clew will then guide you back to your starting point.";


"addingALandmarkTutorialTitle" = "Adding a Landmark - Voice Notes";
"addingALandmarkTutorialTextParagraph1" = "Voice notes allow you to record a landmark or leave specific information that you want to hear later when navigating in the return direction. To leave a voice note:";
"addingALandmarkTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Tap the voice note button at any time that you are recording a route. The app will then open the voice recorder. Press the record button to leave a voice memo.";
"addingALandmarkTutorialTextParagraph3" = "Tap the stop recording button and resume recording your route.";
"addingALandmarkTutorialTextParagraph4" = "When you navigate your route, Clew will play your voice note when you pass through your recorded landmark. You can record as many voice notes as you want.";

"pausingNavigationTutorialTitle" = "Pausing Navigation";
"pausingNavigationTutorialText" = "You can pause Clew if you want to initiate the return navigation at a later time. Pausing Clew will require you to set an 'anchor point'. The anchor point stores important orientation and directional information and is needed to realign you to the correct path. The following module will teach you how to use anchor points.";

"anchorPointsTutorialTitle" = "Setting and Finding Anchor Points";
"anchorPointsTutorialText" = "Setting anchor points is an important skill that is needed in order to save routes or pause navigation. Anchor points allow Clew to record your position and orientation within the route's environment. The anchor point realigns you to the correct path whenever you want to navigate a route that has been saved for later use and they are essential to Clew's navigation accuracy.";

"settingAnAnchorPointTutorialTitle" = "Setting an Anchor Point";
"settingAnAnchorPointTutorialText" = "Anchor points are created at the beginning and at the end of a route. We recommend setting the anchor point at a location that is easy to remember and find at a later time. A good anchor point could be set at a wall, a doorframe, or a piece of furniture like a table.";

"textOrVoiceNotesTutorialTitle" = "Text or Voice Notes";
"textOrVoiceNotesTutorialText" = "Clew allows you to record a text or voice note to describe the location of your anchor point. This can be especially helpful when you want to find and realign yourself to the saved anchor point at a later time.";

"physicalAlignmentTutorialTitle" = "Physical Alignment";
"physicalAlignmentTutorialTextParagraph1" = "Physical alignment sets the anchor point using the phone's inertial sensors. This method requires you to hold the phone in the horizontal or flat pose with the screen facing up, and press the top (short edge) of the phone against a vertical edge, like against a wall, a doorframe or a table.";
"physicalAlignmentTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Press the align button and wait for the countdown. The anchor point will be saved at the end of the countdown.";

"findingAnAnchorPointTutorialTitle" = "Finding an Anchor Point";
"findingAnAnchorPointTutorialTextParagraph1" = "The accuracy of the navigation will depend on how well you can realign yourself to the saved anchor point. To find and realign yourself to a saved anchor point, you should try to position yourself as closely as possible to the exact location of the originally saved anchor point.";
"findingAnAnchorPointTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Finding the saved anchor point from the physical alignment requires you to hold your phone in the same horizontal or flat pose, pressing it against the same edge that was used to set the anchor point.";
"findingAnAnchorPointTutorialTextParagraph3" = "Finding the saved anchor point from the visual alignment simply requires you to hold the phone in the vertical pose and realign the camera to the same location that was used to set the original anchor point.";

"applesARWorldMapTutorialTitle" = "Apple's ARWorld Map";
"applesARWorldMapTutorialTextParagraph1" = "Apple's ARWorld map can help make the process of finding and aligning to a saved anchor point easier. Especially for those that have newer iPhone models and for environments with consistent, artificial lighting, the physical alignment can simply be achieved by holding the phone in the vertical pose. However, we recommend that you be consistent in holding the phone pose and relocalizing yourself as best as possible to the originally saved anchor point in order to ensure the best accuracy from Clew.";

"applesARWorldMapTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Next you will have a chance to practice setting and aligning to anchor points.  Tap the 'Practice' button to start the exercise.";

