"savedRoutesTutorialButtonText" = "Saving and Finding Routes";
"savedRouteTutorialInstructionTextParagraph1" = "Clew allows you to record a route that you can return to at a later time. The Save Routes feature is useful for paths that you want to come back to frequently. The route is stored on your device's memory (and soon on the cloud). You can navigate a saved route from A-to-B and back.";

"savedRouteTutorialInstructionTextParagraph2" = "For example, you can save a route at a hotel which could navigate you from the front desk to the elevator and back. Or from the elevator to your hotel room and back to the elevator.";

"savingARouteTutorialTitle" = "Saving a Route";
"savingARouteTutorialTextParagraph1" = "Saving a route records both the route from points A-to-B, referred to as 'Start-to-End', and the return route, referred to as 'End-to-Start'. Keep this reference in mind whenever you want to navigate a saved route.";
"savingARouteTutorialTextParagraph2" = "Saving a route requires you to set an anchor point at the start of the route. Clew will then record the route until you've reached your destination. You'll then be required to set the anchor point at the end of the route.";
"savingARouteTutorialTextParagraph3" = "Tap the Save Route button in the home screen to begin recording a route.";

"namingYourRouteTutorialTitle" = "Naming your Route";
"namingYourRouteTutorialText" = "Once you've recorded the route and set your end anchor point, Clew will prompt you to name your route. We recommend using a name that best describes the route and that you'll remember at a later time.";

